root

public byte[] root(byte[] nodeContent,
                   boolean isDigest)
Take the content block for which this is the MerklePath, and compute the root digest for verification. The caller then needs to check whether it matches the root, and the root is authentic (signed by a trusted key).

Parameters:
nodeContent - either the content of the block or its digest. If a subclass of MerkleTree overrides computeBlockDigest, a caller must hand in the digest, as this uses the MerkleTree default.
isDigest - was this node already digested, or do we need to digest it
Returns:
the computed root digest
